$interpreted: Izumi: Wow~ Sis Naya is so cool~ I'm about to fall in love with you~
Naya: Quit messing around and start actually helping!
Angelia: ...Everyone, everyone, can you hear me?
Naya: It's a broadcast from the castle!

Angelia: I've arrived at the control room. The Soul Energy from the Dragoneye Gem has been successfully teleported here.
The weapon is now aimed at the monster horde too. What's the progress on your side?
Sherlock: Quit yapping! I literally just removed the core and now you're asking me to put it back! Maybe you shouldn't have told me to remove it from the start!
Naya: Whatever, just hurry up!
Sherlock: Done. Praise the great Sherlock!
Naya: So you're finally done!?
Sherlock: All I have to do now is press this button to activate the Rayzor's mainframe. The princess should be able to receive the command code then. Boop~
Elio: Darn it, we have to activate the Rayzor's mainframe as soon as possible...
Angelia: The monsters are starting to move! Did we not make it in time!?

Angelia: ... Hmm, what does this indicator mean...?
Is Rayzor ready to go? Very well, FIRE!!

Messenger: ...The blazing beam on the kingdom's borders, which came from the direction of Atlas, not only illuminated the night,
but it also caused great panic among civilians.
Messenger: Moreover, some nobles have recognized that it's... it's...
Theodore: Speak.
Messenger: ...They've recognized that it's a beam fired by the Rayzor weapon attached to the castle.
Messenger: Right now, they are concerned that the fallen castle in Atlas is in the hands of malicious people...
Theodore: Understood. Stand down for now. See if you can stop those nobles from spreading baseless rumors.
Messenger: Yes, your Majesty!
Theodore: Nobody is around anymore. You can show yourself now.
Karen: It has been a while, your Majesty.
Theodore: Skip the pleasantries. You're supposed to keep an eye on those lizards at the Bazaar. You better have a good reason for leaving your post.
Karen: I met princess Angelia at Poleva Desert.
Theodore: Angelia!? Why would she be at the Desert!? Is she still there?
Karen: Princess only stayed for a brief period. When she left, she took Commerce Chamber vice president Sherlock with her as well.
Karen: Atlas seemed to be her next destination.
Theodore: ...Then the beam we just witnessed...did Angelia reboot the Rayzor!?

Theodore: How dare that person not report such crucial information to me! Want to betray me now? 
I'll make you pay a steep price!
